Project Description:

We are seeking a Java J2EE Developer in Orlando, FL– Must be local or willing to relocate at own expenses.

This is a contract opportunity that does not offer sponsorship now or in the future.

Must be able to work on W2.

Responsibilities:

Good Knowledge on Java/ J2EE and concepts of threads. good understanding on how to perform thread dumps and heap dumps analysis.

Preferred good Middleware exposure - Linux/Unix commands usage, Scripting/ automation skills.

Preferred Knowledge on any Application servers like Tomcat, WebSphere, Jboss, tcserver, NodeJS, Preferred skill sets on any enterprise monitoring tools - AppD, Wily, Ganglia, Splunk, Newrelic, HP Service Now etc.

Good to have experience on any scripting Language - Perl, python, .

Good to have AWS Experience.

Part of 24x7 operations coverage support for 250+ applications

Restore P1 P2 outages for the business and work on preventative items

Work on automation tools like rundeck, AITR, and work on innovations like Chaos Engineering, etc.

Have a driving personality – driving incidents to resolution across teams. working in complex situations with many apps/infrastructure/different client

Applicants for employment in the US must have work authorization that does not now or in the future require sponsorship of a visa for employment authorization in the United States and with Accenture (i.e., H1-B visa, F-1 visa (OPT), TN visa or any other non-immigrant status).
